message: >
  If you reference this work in research, publications, or implementations,
  please cite it using the metadata below.
type: software
title: "Governed Decision Intelligence: The Decision Architecture for Governed AI"
abstract: >
  An open specification and Python reference implementation for recording the
  authority, evidence, uncertainty, alternatives, gate classification, and
  escalation conditions surrounding consequential AI-assisted decisions before
  execution. The repository includes a Governed Decision Record schema,
  deterministic gate-classification tests, worked examples, and an experimental
  signed-receipt interoperability driver. External conformance review and field
  validation remain pending.
